olive oil
1 bag green beans
1 carrot
1 packet udon noodles
1 packet char siu paste
1 packet oyster sauce
1 tbs soy sauce
1 tbs sesame oil
½ lemon
1 packet beef mince
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
1 head Asian Greens
2 clove garlic

• Bring a medium saucepan of water to the boil.
• Trim and halve green beans. Thinly slice carrot into half-moons. Roughly chop Asian greens. Finely chop garlic. Slice the lemon into wedges.
• In a small bowl, combine char siu paste, oyster sauce, soy sauce, sesame oil, a squeeze of lemon juice and a dash of water. Set aside.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Cook green beans and carrot until softened, 4-5 minutes. Add Asian greens and cook until wilted, 1-2 minutes. Transfer to a plate.
• Meanwhile, cook udon noodles in the boiling water, stirring occasionally with a fork to separate, until softened, 2 minutes. Drain and refresh under cold water.

TIP: Add a dash of water to the veggies to help speed up the cooking process.

• Return the frying pan to a high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook beef mince, breaking it up with a spoon, until just browned, 2-3 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes. Add veggies, udon noodles and char siu sauce mixture and simmer until combined, 1-2 minutes. Season to taste.

• Divide char siu beef and udon noodles between plates.
• Top with crushed peanuts. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges.